You guys have shown us a great amount of passion and enthusiam. People have turned out in large numbers for the interviews. So, we couldn't finish the Round 1 today. For the people who couldn't give the Round 1 today, you can come tomorrow at 10am. Try coming as early as possible. People coming after round 2 begins will not be entertained.

Round 2 will begin from 11am. People who are selected for the second round will be mailed by tonight.

Selections are going on for all the three teams. Here is the detailed venue.

Mechanical team - F132
Embedded team - F234
AI team - F244

See you all !

You have been a fantastic audience today! We are looking for a team with great zeal and passion for being our successors! Be there tomorrow to be a part of our team so that we can know you better!
Register here - https://tinyurl.com/krssg-2019

Round 1 will be held on 2nd Feb (Saturday) and round 2 on 3rd Feb (Sunday). People who qualify in round 1 will be eligible for interviews in round 2. More details in the poster. 

Share this information with your friends too so that they also don't miss out this golden opportunity. 
Good luck!

Problem-solving in complex domains often involves multiple agents, dynamic environments, and the need for learning from previous experience. Robotic soccer is an example of such a complex environment.
"Code-O-Soccer", a simulation-based strategic coding event, is back again to provide you with the platform where you code the match strategy for a team of three robots and show your coding skills!

Prizes Worth - ₹50,000/-
Register at: https://ktj.in/codeconclave
For more details visit: http://event.krssg.in/

Join our Facebook forum to get the insight on the event:- http://tinyurl.com/code-o-soccer (Any doubt can be asked here)

Submit your codes before 7th January 2019

We hope to inspire more such students across India to be a part of the astounding world of robotics.
